/* #18345 changed */
@50  = ~There's quite a bit to say, I don't really know if I have the time to go into all of the details. I used to live at Candlekeep with my father Gorion. A little while back we were forced to flee. Someone was out there who really wanted me dead. In trying to kill me, he... killed my dad.~
/* #18351 changed */
@51  = ~I am sorry to bring back such painful memories. I wish to help you, and in doing so, end these dreams that plague me. Here, take this. Goodbye now. Perhaps we shall meet again.~
@52  = ~Ah, <CHARNAME>! I am so relieved that the hubbub is over. It was a bad feeling, being ordered to fight you, after seeing how Duke Eltan trusted you the way he did before Angelo took over...~
@53  = ~And thank you, *thank you* for saving our commander.~
@54  = ~We will mourn our losses while we gather what is left after Sarevok and his minions besmirched the Flaming Fist like they did, making us his tools. Thank you for saving this city, hero.~
@55  = ~Seems fighting you wasn't the right thing to do after all. Well, who would have thought that Angelo and Sarevok would play such a wrong game. It seems you saved us from dark times, indeed.~
